    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>Do you have too long text elements sticking out and breaking the web site layout?</p>\n<p>If you have such a problem, fix their length by specifying the elements with CSS selectors.</p>\n<p>Notes: you need a basic understanding of CSS (jQuery) selectors to use this plugin.</p>\n<h4>Supported Language</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>English</li>\n</ul>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload <strong><code>text-truncator.php</code></strong> and other files compressed in the zip folder to the <strong><code>/wp-content/plugins/</code></strong> directory.</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress.</li>\n<li>Go to <strong>Dashboard</strong> -&gt; <strong>Appearance</strong> -&gt; <strong>Truncator</strong>.</li>\n<li>Configure the options by setting a selector and height.</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1 &#8211; 07/05/2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Released.</li>\n</ul>\n"
    },
    "short_description": "Truncates text of specified HTML elements by number of lines.",
